              { q:"How do I automate my Shopify store in 2026?", a:"Use the $0 Automation Stack: Make.com free tier as the central webhook hub, CAPI Shield for server-side ad tracking, Stocky Swap for inventory management, Systeme.io for email automation, and Google Apps Script Quota Fix for document workflow stability. The complete setup takes 35 minutes and costs $0/month for stores processing under 200 orders per month." },
              { q:"Why did my Shopify ROAS drop in January 2026?", a:'Two events hit simultaneously: iOS 26 stripped fbclid parameters from Private Browsing links and links shared via Mail and Messages, breaking click-level attribution. On January 13 2026, Shopify changed App Pixels to "Optimised" mode — silently throttling third-party tracking pixel data. Together these create a 30–45% conversion data gap. Server-side tracking via CAPI Shield fixes both issues simultaneously.' },
              { q:"What happened to Shopify's pixel on January 13 2026?", a:'Shopify changed App Pixels to "Optimised" mode on January 13 2026. This change throttles the data that third-party pixel apps receive from Shopify\'s checkout events — without throwing an error or notifying merchants. Server-side tracking via CAPI Shield bypasses the App Pixel system entirely.' },
              { q:"When does Shopify Stocky retire?", a:"Shopify Stocky retires on August 31 2026. After this date, all stores lose access to the app and all inventory data held within it. Export your data now via Stocky → Settings → Export, then deploy Stocky Swap as your replacement. The migration takes 4 minutes and your data lives in a Google Sheet you own permanently." },
              { q:"How do I automate my Shopify store for free?", a:"Use the $0 Automation Stack: Make.com (free tier) as the central hub, Google Sheets for inventory, the Conversions API for tracking, and Systeme.io for email marketing. This replaces paid tracking, inventory, automation, and email apps at zero cost. Deploy in under 35 minutes with no code." },
              { q:"Make.com vs Zapier for Shopify?", a:"Make.com. It offers 1,000 free operations per month versus Zapier's 100, supports multi-step workflows on the free tier, and handles Shopify webhooks in real time (Zapier's free tier polls every 15 minutes). For Shopify automation specifically, Make.com is the stronger choice at every price point." },
              { q:"How do I replace Shopify Stocky for free?", a:"Use Stocky Swap — a free Make.com workflow that logs every Shopify order to a Google Sheet in real time. It replicates Stocky's core inventory tracking functionality at $0/month, supports multi-location inventory, and stores all data in a Google Sheet you own. Deploy before August 31 2026." },
              { q:"Can I automate Shopify without coding?", a:"Yes. The entire $0 Automation Stack requires zero coding. Make.com uses a visual drag-and-drop builder, Google Sheets requires no scripting for basic inventory tracking, and the Conversions API integration is configured via point-and-click webhook setup in Shopify Admin." },
              { q:"What is Klaviyo's billing change and how does it affect my costs?", a:"In February 2025, Klaviyo changed to billing on all active profiles — including unengaged contacts. Stores with large historical email lists saw their bill increase significantly. Systeme.io's free plan provides unlimited contacts and email sends with no profile billing surprises." },
              { q:"How do I get my Shopify store found by ChatGPT and Google AI Mode?", a:"Optimise for Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO): add structured product schema markup, create FAQ content that matches conversational queries, and ensure your product data is programmatically accessible. AI-driven traffic to Shopify grew 8x year-on-year in 2025." },
              { q:"What are Shopify Agentic Storefronts?", a:"Shopify Agentic Storefronts allow customers to complete purchases directly inside ChatGPT, Google AI Mode, and Microsoft Copilot. Currently US-only early access, enabled via the Knowledge Base App (free for Shopify Plus, $50/month for standard plans)." },
              { q:"What is Shopify automation?", a:"Shopify automation connects Shopify to external tools via webhooks and APIs so that repetitive tasks — order logging, ad tracking, inventory updates, email sequences — happen automatically without manual work or paid app subscriptions." },
              { q:"How much can I save by automating my Shopify store?", a:"Most stores save $500–$900 per month by replacing paid tracking apps ($149–$299/mo), inventory apps ($29–$449/mo), automation connectors ($49–$99/mo), and email marketing tools ($45–$400/mo) with the free stack." },
